      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a collector-grade specimen featuring the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine. The sequential twin-turbochargers provide a seamless power band, with the secondary transition occurring precisely at 4,500 RPM. The chassis remains incredibly rigid, benefiting from a near-perfect 50/50 weight distribution and a factory-spec double-wishbone suspension setup. Mechanically, the apex seals show optimal compression across all faces, and the cooling system has been meticulously maintained to prevent heat soak. Finished in pristine Montego Blue, this FD retains its factory Torsen limited-slip differential and five-speed manual transmission with crisp, short-throw engagement. A true driver\u2019s car preserved in its most purist form, free of any aftermarket modifications or structural fatigue.",
